<TITLE> BTTB's reduced internet charges effective from Feb 1 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 3 (bdnews24.com)  The reduced charges for submarine cable-based internet bandwidth will be effective from Feb 1, BTTB officials said Sunday. Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission and Bangladesh Telegraph and Telephone Board had approved a proposal in this regard on Jan 27. A BTTB public relations officer said setting up an international private lease circuit or IPLC above two megabytes per second now costs Tk 75,000, instead of Tk 90,000. Individual users will pay BBTB Tk 1,000 instead of Tk 1,400 for unlimited internet use, effective Feb 1, while the monthly fee for the 'OfficeMate' package will be reduced to Tk 700 from Tk 1,000 and the 'OfficePack' to Tk 700 from Tk 750. The minimum charge for installing a leased internet access service above two mbps bandwidth has been reduced to Tk 20,000 from Tk 30,000. Minimum monthly charge for bandwidth is between Tk 32,000 and 40,000. Minimum charge for leased internet access by submarine cable up to two mbps is Tk 96,000, down from Tk 1.65 lakh. A newly launched STM-1 service will charge a registration fee of Tk 20,000, installation and testing fee of Tk 1 lakh and bilateral voice charge of $ 40,000. In addition, STM-1 internet access by satellite, also newly launched by BTTB, will charge a registration fee for bandwidth from one mbps to 15 mbps of Tk 10,000, installation and testing fee of Tk 10,000 to 30,000, and a monthly charge from Tk 1.05 lakh to 1.15 lakh. bdnews
